{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/notion/using-formulas-to-calculate-weight/","webpackCompilationHash":"af3a53244b354de16405","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Kylie's Blog","author":"Kylie Stewart","siteUrl":"https://kyliestewart.tech/blog","sponsor":{"buyMeACoffeeId":""}}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"a1c52148-1b27-58b7-862d-40763276ad15","excerpt":"Calculating Pack Weight in Notion Over the weekend, I decided to formally document all of my backpacking, camping, hiking, and climbing gear. I wanted to create a centralized tracker for a few reasons, the most important few being: Figuring out when it’s time to replace a piece…","html":"<h1 id=\"calculating-pack-weight-in-notion\"><a href=\"#calculating-pack-weight-in-notion\" aria-label=\"calculating pack weight in notion permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Calculating Pack Weight in Notion</h1>\n<p>Over the weekend, I decided to formally document all of my backpacking, camping, hiking, and climbing gear. I wanted to create a centralized tracker for a few reasons, the most important few being:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Figuring out when it’s time to replace a piece of gear, based on the length of time I’ve owned it and condition it’s currently in</li>\n<li>Tracking the weight of my pack, dependent on trip type (i.e. backpacking trips require different gear than day hikes)</li>\n</ul>\n<p>I haven’t used Notion as an inventory source for my possessions before, so I browsed the <a href=\"https://www.notion.so/Notion-Template-Gallery-181e961aeb5c4ee6915307c0dfd5156d\">template gallery</a> for inspiration. This <a href=\"https://www.notion.so/Plant-tracker-faafcfcf6a9d4f10b579d9351ecaaebc\">plant tracker</a> from <a href=\"https://twitter.com/yuemaggie\">@maggieyue</a> looked like a good template to duplicate for something like this, so I went for it. I made a few changes to the plant tracker (while also maintaining a separate duplicate of the plant tracker for <a href=\"https://www.notion.so/kalestew/Plants-3e733a7a27e248c79f22042032411a7b\">my own plants</a> because this template is awesome), but overall I found it served my needs very well.</p>\n<h2 id=\"changes-made\"><a href=\"#changes-made\" aria-label=\"changes made permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Changes Made</h2>\n<p>I only made a handful of changes transitioning the <a href=\"https://www.notion.so/Plant-tracker-faafcfcf6a9d4f10b579d9351ecaaebc\">Plant Tracker</a> into a <a href=\"https://www.notion.so/kalestew/abebdb4997514ef8882e13b1d00baebf?v=6691b68442e64533a85138d04b75912d\">Gear Tracker</a>.</p>\n<p>Properties I kept</p>\n<ul>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">Acquisition Date</code> - I found this could represent the same piece of data for both tables</li>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">Name</code> - as an identifying column, it doesn’t get much simpler than a simple name</li>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">Visual</code> - attaching an image of the item is a nice organizational step</li>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">Care &amp; Notes</code> - turned into just a plain <code class=\"language-text\">Notes</code> but kept it for quick reminders</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Properties I added</p>\n<ul>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">URL</code> - a link to the product or the latest version of the product, if applicable</li>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">Weight (oz)</code> - I’ve found it’s easier to obtain a weight in ounces and then convert it to pounds, but this might not be the case for a different variety of item you are trying to inventory</li>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">Weight (lb)</code> - a formula that relates to the weight in ounces and divides it by 16, so I can sum both columns separately</li>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">Category</code> - options include <code class=\"language-text\">Backpacking</code>, <code class=\"language-text\">Car Camping</code>, <code class=\"language-text\">Day Hike</code>, etc. - allows me to sort items by trip type (see <a href=\"#views\">Views</a> for more details)</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Properties I got rid of</p>\n<ul>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">Botanical Name</code>, <code class=\"language-text\">Date Watered</code>, <code class=\"language-text\">Date Fertilized</code>, and <code class=\"language-text\">Water Propogation</code> - for obvious reasons</li>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">Location</code> and <code class=\"language-text\">Location Notes</code> - the location of my gear when I’m not using it doesn’t matter quite as much as it does with plants</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"views\"><a href=\"#views\" aria-label=\"views permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Views</h2>\n<p>Hinging around the <code class=\"language-text\">Category</code> property, I’ve created a few different views of this Gear table to serve as a packing list of sorts for various activities.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 280px;\"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 99.64285714285715%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"List of views\"\n        title=\"List of views\"\n        src=\"/blog/static/7acea4a0193a0cc01f728818ab011333/8af66/gear-views.png\"\n        srcset=\"/blog/static/7acea4a0193a0cc01f728818ab011333/cf440/gear-views.png 148w,\n/blog/static/7acea4a0193a0cc01f728818ab011333/8af66/gear-views.png 280w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 280px) 100vw, 280px\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n    </span></p>\n<p>When one navigates to the view, it’s filtered down to the appropriate category and I’ve hidden that property column entirely to clean up the view.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 590px;\"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 44.8151487826871%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"14er packing list\"\n        title=\"14er packing list\"\n        src=\"/blog/static/f5ed4893eb34d5469cb96ea8839856c4/b9e4f/gear-14er-list.png\"\n        srcset=\"/blog/static/f5ed4893eb34d5469cb96ea8839856c4/cf440/gear-14er-list.png 148w,\n/blog/static/f5ed4893eb34d5469cb96ea8839856c4/d2d38/gear-14er-list.png 295w,\n/blog/static/f5ed4893eb34d5469cb96ea8839856c4/b9e4f/gear-14er-list.png 590w,\n/blog/static/f5ed4893eb34d5469cb96ea8839856c4/f9b6a/gear-14er-list.png 885w,\n/blog/static/f5ed4893eb34d5469cb96ea8839856c4/2d849/gear-14er-list.png 1180w,\n/blog/static/f5ed4893eb34d5469cb96ea8839856c4/9519f/gear-14er-list.png 2218w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n    </span></p>\n<h2 id=\"in-conclusion\"><a href=\"#in-conclusion\" aria-label=\"in conclusion permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>In Conclusion</h2>\n<p>It’s very simple to appropriate a template for your own uses, if you’re willing to make some small changes. Thanks to flexibility of databases within Notion, it’s also very simple to change the way you consume that data.</p>\n<p>Thanks for reading about my Gear Tracker and the approach I took to get here! Check out <a href=\"https://www.kyliestewart.tech/blog\">my other Notion posts</a> for more organizational fun.</p>","frontmatter":{"title":"Using Formulas to Calculate Weight","date":"August 16, 2019"}}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false,"slug":"/notion/using-formulas-to-calculate-weight/","previous":null,"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/notion/my-personal-wiki/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"How I Use Notion as a Personal Wiki","category":"notion"}}}}}